    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: P16E5"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "",
      "text": "DTC P16E5: LIN communication error（DCDC)"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "83_3.0_jpn_11033596_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "LIN for DC-DC converters uses a master-slave system: only one control unit becomes the master control unit (PGM-FI ECU) and manages all signals on the LIN bus. The slave unit (DC-DC converter) functions by signals from the master node. If the signal sent using LIN cannot be received for a predetermined period of time or if the information sent using LIN remains abnormal for a predetermined period of time, the PGM-FI ECU determines that a failure has occurred and stores the DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection frequency, detection sequence, detection time required, detection method type, OBD status"
    },
    {
